  "informal_statement": "For a finite type alpha, a function f : alpha -> alpha is injective if and only if it is surjective (the pigeonhole-principle corollary for finite self-maps).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Direct application of Mathlib's Finite.injective_iff_surjective.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem finite_injective_iff_surjective (α : Type) [Finite α] (f : α → α) : Function.Injective f ↔ Function.Surjective f",
