  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode 1cace84e), kernel_verified on the first attempt. All prior injective/surjective packets in this domain (`injective_comp`, `surjective_comp`, `strictmono_injective`, `bijective_comp`, `left_inverse_injective`/`right_inverse_surjective`) work over arbitrary (possibly infinite) types, where injective and surjective are independent properties -- this packet adds the classic FINITE-endofunction special case (pigeonhole principle) where the two coincide, a genuinely distinct fact worth its own packet. Confirmed via `grep -rl 'Fintype\\|Finite'` (no real hits) that this angle wasn't covered yet.",
